        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 15 at 4:29PM PDT by NWS Elko NV</headline>
        <description>At 428 PM PDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Elko, moving northeast at 25 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and half inch hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Brief heavy rainfall along with gusty winds could knock
down tree limbs and blow around unsecured objects. Minor
hail damage to vegetation is possible.

Locations impacted include...
Elko, Ryndon, Spring Creek, Adobe Summit, and Lamoille Summit.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
